      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying San Marino",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/0_rsm.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Monte_Titano.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/vUPiUkLWrGB1KzXC8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The 739m-tall **Monte Titano** dominates the surrounding landscape and is visible from almost every point in the Republic.",
              "NOTE: Look for the **three towers** to safely identify it."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Landscape.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/1cqVe47FmXH9gp6bA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The landscape of San Marino largely consists of smooth **agricultural hills**, with many small winding roads. The vegetation is distinctly **Mediterranean**, and normally appears quite lush."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_License_Plate.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_License_Plate.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Sammarinese licence plates are **short**, **white** and have **blue lettering** on them.",
              "NOTE: Other European countries will typically have **longer** licence plates, often with one or more **blue strips**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Italian_infrastructure.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/5VD2pzJLT1RXj8PCA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Road signs and bollards are **generally identical** to the ones used in Italy.",
              "NOTE: Many road signs give directions to the nearby Italian city of **Rimini**."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "bollard"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Poles.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/we7AJ1yxXcfgqLLz9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Just like Italy, most utility poles in San Marino are **round **and made** **of **concrete. **Wooden poles are also found in the country."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "pole"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Chevron.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/bM4E51AfrGfBSFaX8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "San Marino is the only country in the world to use **yellow **chevrons with **burgundy red **arrows."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Pedestrian_Crossing.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/JNpdbvUsjLXyrEuW8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "These **elaborate pedestrian crossings**, with painted blue crosswalks and hanging signs, are specific to San Marino."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_Trash_Bins.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/Jr3mAXsrTXH3BojV7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**Lime-green bins** are particularly common in San Marino. In Generation 4 coverage some of them have been replaced by **black **bins."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/san-marino/San_Marino_divided_road.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/i8B3TJE5iChF9pWt8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The Superstrada di San Marino runs from the border village of Dogana to the City of San Marino. It is the **only divided road** in the country, and the lanes are separated by a **metal guardrail**."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "guardrail"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
